01:18:19.962 --> 01:18:21.524
we were deceived.

731
01:18:21.524 --> 01:18:26.320
Shelby is a safe town. if something
like this could happen here.

732
01:18:26.320 --> 01:18:29.321
think how bad it must be out there

733
01:18:46.480 --> 01:18:47.779
Roberta. it's okay

734
01:18:47.779 --> 01:18:57.586
No. it's not okay! Why did they have
to die? Why did she have to die?

735
01:18:59.502 --> 01:19:07.615
My dad lied to me. said these beautiful angels
moved to earth and carried her away

736
01:19:07.615 --> 01:19:10.960
Before she's started to feel any pain

737
01:19:17.508 --> 01:19:23.101
- Why did she have to die?
- Why did he have to lie to me?

738
01:19:26.635 --> 01:19:29.665
He's all I have left any more

739
01:19:41.592 --> 01:19:44.073
It's not all you have left.

740
01:19:56.095 --> 01:19:58.688
All I can count on is you guys

741
01:20:01.918 --> 01:20:05.985
- I know how you feel.
- What do you mean?

742
01:20:10.282 --> 01:20:14.734
- My dad moved out. they are getting a divorce. 
- A divorce?

743
01:20:15.656 --> 01:20:16.968
I'm sorry. Sam

744
01:20:18.978 --> 01:20:23.979
Screw them. You guys have us

745
01:20:25.576 --> 01:20:35.025
I say we make a pact. here and now. We're here for
each other always no matter what happens in life ...

746
01:20:36.586 --> 01:20:45.618
If Teeny goes off to Hollywood or I marry a rich
doctor. we'll remember this day and this pact

747
01:20:45.618 --> 01:20:56.122
whenever we need a friend we're here for each
other. we can count on it. always. no matter what

748
01:20:57.652 --> 01:20:59.948
It's a pact

749
01:21:00.779 --> 01:21:04.126
- All for one.
- And one for all.

750
01:21:05.690 --> 01:21:08.692
Now more than ever we need to
put Dear Johnny to rest

751
01:21:09.251 --> 01:21:11.597
- Everyone ready?
- Ready

752
01:21:17.167 --> 01:21:21.807
We brought Dear Johnny back from the
dead and it's up to us to send him home

753
01:21:21.807 --> 01:21:23.808
Close your eyes

754
01:21:27.606 --> 01:21:35.256
Guide us in our pursuit of the spirit world. keep our
circle safe from those who promote evil and seek to harm

755
01:21:35.671 --> 01:21:40.111
Dear Johnny. we know you and your
mother were brutally murdered ...

756
01:21:40.111 --> 01:21:47.205
Did you came back to tell us who did it? We're here
to help you rest in peace. Johnny. We're listening

757
01:21:49.070 --> 01:21:50.173
He's here

758
01:21:51.459 --> 01:21:52.947
Don't break the circle.

759
01:21:54.228 --> 01:21:56.834
Tell us who did it. Johnny.
we're here to help

760
01:21:59.835 --> 01:22:01.835
Holy Molly!

761
01:22:12.673 --> 01:22:16.319
- That's the killer
- Please don't hurt us!

762
01:22:16.752 --> 01:22:21.593
Hey. this isn't a playground.
it's a cemetery

763
01:22:24.020 --> 01:22:26.542
And you kids should have a litte respect
for the dead

764
01:22:27.043 --> 01:22:30.703
- Hey. we have a lot of respect for the dead. okay? 
- Yeah. that's why we're here

765
01:22:30.703 --> 01:22:33.960
- We resurrected Dear Johnny from the grave
- Oh really?

766
01:22:34.369 --> 01:22:37.355
How do you think his tombstone
got cracked on the middle?

767
01:22:38.539 --> 01:22:41.429
I.. knocked it over with my tractor

768
01:22:43.706 --> 01:22:49.538
- You did?
- Yeah. a-ha. it's not easy moving around all these headstones

769
01:23:08.665 --> 01:23:13.651
I'm not doing anymore of these dumb
seances. they are a waste of time

770
01:23:13.863 --> 01:23:16.551
I can't believe how we did it

771
01:23:17.782 --> 01:23:20.689
- What about the tarot cards. then?
- Get over it

772
01:23:35.602 --> 01:23:39.317
I knew at that moment our days
of playing make-believe were over

773
01:23:40.515 --> 01:23:43.736
As we grow older it becomes difficult
to just believe

774
01:23:44.606 --> 01:23:49.453
It's not that we don't want to. but
too much has happened that we can't

775
01:24:05.721 --> 01:24:06.941
Let's go

776
01:24:08.925 --> 01:24:11.307
Hey look. it's Crazy Pete

777
01:24:13.859 --> 01:24:15.994
Let's leave him alone. okay?

778
01:24:35.167 --> 01:24:39.628
- What's wrong?
- I forgot something in the cemetery. I'll catch up

779
01:24:39.865 --> 01:24:42.568
- You want me to come with you?
- No. I'll be okay

780
01:25:11.298 --> 01:25:12.295
Pete?

781
01:25:22.289 --> 01:25:23.647
You're Peter Simms?

782
01:25:30.359 --> 01:25:32.056
They were my family.

783
01:25:35.384 --> 01:25:40.125
It's a terrible thing that happened to
them. I'm sorry

784
01:25:42.077 --> 01:25:51.470
For the longest time I thought I could've stopped him.
if I would've been home instead of down at that bar

785
01:25:57.746 --> 01:26:00.109
But you were there for me

786
01:26:04.951 --> 01:26:15.594
I've wasted a lot of years. afraid to face people.
mostly afraid to face myself

787
01:26:27.394 --> 01:26:29.021
I'm scared too

788
01:26:34.248 --> 01:26:37.846
- What's your name?
- Samantha

789
01:26:38.826 --> 01:26:45.500
Well. Samantha. things will happen
in your life that you can't stop...

790
01:26:45.500 --> 01:26:54.358
but that's no reason to shut out the world.
there's a purpose for the good and for the bad

791
01:27:09.023 --> 01:27:15.316
He gave me the only gift he could. the
lesson that had taken him a lifetime to learn

792
01:27:15.316 --> 01:27:23.190
And although I understood the importance of his words.
it's only now. looking back. that I understand their meaning

793
01:27:24.314 --> 01:27:26.958
Rest in peace. Dear Johnny

794
01:28:06.840 --> 01:28:09.256
- Do I look better with this?
- Yeah. right.

795
01:28:14.006 --> 01:28:19.634
We all used to try so hard to fit in. We wanted
to look exactly alike. do all the same things.

796
01:28:19.634 --> 01:28:27.182
Practically be the same people. and when we weren't
looking. that changed. the tree house was supposed

797
01:28:27.182 --> 01:28:33.573
to bring us more independence. but what the summer
actually brought was independence from each other

798
01:28:36.788 --> 01:28:37.740
Samantha!

799
01:28:38.507 --> 01:28:39.882
Samantha!

800
01:28:41.869 --> 01:28:43.123
Samantha!

801
01:28:43.526 --> 01:28:44.539
Samantha!

802
01:28:44.808 --> 01:28:48.399
- What?
- Your car's blocking my jeep

803
01:28:48.399 --> 01:28:51.468
- Oh shit!
- It's coming. I think I saw its head

804
01:28:51.468 --> 01:28:53.289
- You saw it's head?
- You can see its head?

805
01:28:53.289 --> 01:28:54.508
You didn't see its head

806
01:28:54.508 --> 01:28:57.194
- I'll get the keys.
- No. forget the keys. take the limo

807
01:28:57.194 --> 01:28:58.913
- The limo?
- Take the limo.

808
01:28:58.913 --> 01:29:01.777
We'll take your limo. go get the
bags. call Morton

809
01:29:01.777 --> 01:29:04.778
- Ok.
- No. wait. don't leave me alone.

810
01:29:05.872 --> 01:29:08.646
Get the car before another
of those bits

811
01:29:11.273 --> 01:29:12.626
- How you doing?
- Hi

812
01:29:12.626 --> 01:29:14.386
- Get out. I need your car
- Pardon me?

813
01:29:14.386 --> 01:29:16.854
I have a pregnant lady here and I
have to get her to the hospital

814
01:29:16.854 --> 01:29:19.947
No problem. tell me where it is
and I'll get you there in a jiffy

815
01:29:19.947 --> 01:29:21.490
Well. jiffy is not good enough

816
01:29:21.767 --> 01:29:23.243
Move out. bastard!

817
01:29:23.243 --> 01:29:24.673
See?

818
01:29:25.892 --> 01:29:27.008
Thank you very much.

819
01:29:29.144 --> 01:29:30.834
- Just tell him his wife's getting a baby.
- Have a nice day.

820
01:29:32.072 --> 01:29:32.866
Go!

821
01:29:39.038 --> 01:29:41.029
- This is pretty good suspension!
- Sorry!

822
01:29:42.427 --> 01:29:45.194
Morton is in the middle of a root canal
but he'll meet us at the hospital

823
01:29:45.194 --> 01:29:46.901
There is cool room back here

824
01:29:49.504 --> 01:29:53.196
- You should be doing this?
- There is a VCR... I can't believe there is a VCR

825
01:29:53.528 --> 01:29:57.709
- Roberta. there's a VCR in here!
- Yeah. does it have a remote?

826
01:29:59.990 --> 01:30:04.238
Okay. enough screaming. thank you
Breathe. breathe!

827
01:30:06.207 --> 01:30:10.692
- Chrissy. your uncle!
- Oh shit!

828
01:30:10.692 --> 01:30:12.758
No swearing around my baby

829
01:30:12.758 --> 01:30:13.598
Shiiit!

830
01:30:16.078 --> 01:30:18.865
Chris you're gonna have to push
Come on Chrissy. push

831
01:30:21.542 --> 01:30:22.950
I changed my mind about the drugs

832
01:30:22.950 --> 01:30:25.207
- It's too late for that.
- Give me the drugs or I'll kill you!

833
01:30:25.207 --> 01:30:29.024
- Give her the drugs. just give her the drugs!
- Hey. you're gonna have to calm down. all right?

834
01:30:29.024 --> 01:30:31.073
Now push. Chris. push!

835
01:30:34.161 --> 01:30:36.467
Come on. I can see the head. I see the head

836
01:30:38.954 --> 01:30:41.140
You really can see its little head

837
01:30:42.237 --> 01:30:45.704
- Is it supposed to look like that?
- Yes. Chris you're doing great

838
01:30:45.704 --> 01:30:48.581
- Is it a boy or a girl?
- I don't know. so far it's just a head

839
01:30:48.581 --> 01:30:52.083
All right. we're almost there.
one more big one. Chris. you can do it!

840
01:30:53.084 --> 01:30:55.084
Here comes the big one. Chrissy.
push. you're almost there.

841
01:30:55.084 --> 01:30:58.085
you're almost there. one more
big one. Chris. come on!

842
01:31:03.634 --> 01:31:07.926
- I want it out. get out. get out!
- Get it out of her. get it out of her!

843
01:31:11.116 --> 01:31:14.270
It's a girl. a beautiful baby girl

844
01:31:18.707 --> 01:31:20.334
My baby.

845
01:31:38.636 --> 01:31:43.211
- Am I too late?
- No Morton. get your baby

846
01:31:44.212 --> 01:31:50.305
- Hello. dear
- We have a baby girl

847
01:31:58.459 --> 01:31:59.299
Thanks.

848
01:32:00.833 --> 01:32:01.550
You're welcome.

849
01:32:29.466 --> 01:32:33.405
- See?
- She really is beautiful

850
01:32:34.175 --> 01:32:38.280
- You know. kinda looks like a Russian limo!
- Very funny. Roberta!

851
01:32:38.545 --> 01:32:41.502
Chrissy ... truth or dare?

852
01:32:43.501 --> 01:32:46.749
- Truth
- Are you happy?

853
01:32:46.994 --> 01:32:52.002
Yes! I'm so happy I feel like just
bust and shoot happiness all over everywhere

854
01:32:54.274 --> 01:32:57.408
- Roberta. truth or dare?
- Truth

855
01:32:57.408 --> 01:32:59.817
Just how big are your boobs now?

856
01:32:59.817 --> 01:33:04.788
- Well. just how big are your boobs?
- 36 D and worth every penny.

857
01:33:06.848 --> 01:33:09.880
- D? Oh no.
- Sam. truth or dare?

858
01:33:10.899 --> 01:33:14.725
- Truth
- Are you happy?

859
01:33:15.037 --> 01:33:20.474
Not really. but I just figure that it's
normal for things to be shitty

860
01:33:23.664 --> 01:33:29.396
Look. I got A+ on career day. I must've
missed that class on personal relationships

861
01:33:29.396 --> 01:33:34.632
Maybe you should integate color into
your wardrobe. men love pastels on a woman

862
01:33:36.655 --> 01:33:40.196
It's not about pastels or men.
it's about me

863
01:33:42.386 --> 01:33:44.314
What are you talking about Sam?

864
01:33:45.948 --> 01:33:52.175
I've had how many relationships and how
many years. and I've run from every one of them

865
01:33:52.175 --> 01:33:54.176
which doesn't make it easy
to get to that next level

866
01:33:55.416 --> 01:34:00.408
- The intimacy level
- Well. if you don't fall in love. you can't get hurt

867
01:34:01.028 --> 01:34:03.195
But it sure is lonely all by yourself

868
01:34:05.402 --> 01:34:07.102
Yeah. it is

869
01:34:10.075 --> 01:34:15.481
- Hey. you guys remember that summer with Crazy Pete?
- God. we loved a mystery. didn't we?

870
01:34:16.078 --> 01:34:20.047
- Did we have fun that summer or what?
- Yeah. it was the best.

871
01:34:20.047 --> 01:34:24.739
You know I used to send Crazy Pete a
Christmas card every year with some cash

872
01:34:24.739 --> 01:34:26.740
They came back last year

873
01:34:27.077 --> 01:34:29.031
Yeah. he died

874
01:34:31.944 --> 01:34:35.674
You know. I never told you guys this.
but Pete was Dear Johnny's father

875
01:34:35.674 --> 01:34:37.454
- What?
- He was?

876
01:34:37.454 --> 01:34:38.515
How did you know that?

877
01:34:38.515 --> 01:34:44.181
Do you remember our last seance in the cemetery? 
I went back and Pete was there putting flowers on Johnny's grave

878
01:34:46.101 --> 01:34:49.738
He said something that didn't mean
as much then as it does now

879
01:34:50.959 --> 01:34:58.207
He told me that things happe in life that you can't stop. 
but it wasn't a reason to shut out the world.

880
01:35:04.997 --> 01:35:10.809
I realized that I've been so
afraid of the bad things that

881
01:35:13.055 --> 01:35:15.324
that I missed the good

882
01:35:17.709 --> 01:35:19.713
You know I didn't wanna come
back here

883
01:35:22.369 --> 01:35:24.509
But I'm really glad I did

884
01:35:26.338 --> 01:35:29.920
I've forgotten how much it helped
to have you guys as friends

885
01:35:32.283 --> 01:35:36.945
We're really lucky to have this place.
and each other

886
01:35:42.539 --> 01:35:45.866
Boy. there is a part of me that
would like just to stay here forever

887
01:35:45.866 --> 01:35:48.167
I wouldn't go that far

888
01:35:49.482 --> 01:35:54.116
- But it would be nice to come back
and visit more often

889
01:35:54.116 --> 01:35:55.517
I agree

890
01:35:56.607 --> 01:35:59.013
Let's make a pact

891
01:35:59.013 --> 01:36:02.014
("Now And Then" by Susanna Hoffs)

892
01:36:05.650 --> 01:36:09.885
- All for one.
- And one for all.

893
01:36:25.961 --> 01:36:27.027
Come on!

894
01:36:27.027 --> 01:36:30.668
You can run from the disappointments
to try to forget...

895
01:36:31.573 --> 01:36:35.356
But it's only when you embrace your
past that you truly move forward

896
01:36:36.917 --> 01:36:39.701
Maybe Thomas Wolf never got to go
home again

897
01:36:39.701 --> 01:36:43.104
But I found my way there.
and I'm glad I did
